Jeff,

The &quot;flame&quot; object has a function named &quot;restore&quot;.

the syntax ( from the help(BurnerFlame) ) is:

flame = BurnerFlame(gas = gas, grid = grid)
flame.restore( file = &quot;soln.xml&quot;, id = &quot;solution&quot;)

where the arguments in the  function mirror those in the &quot;save&quot;
function:

flame.save( file = &quot;soln.xml&quot;, id = &quot;solution&quot;, desc = &quot;none&quot;)

A note is that the save function does not over-write a previously saved
solution in
the save file.  Instead the solution is saved with to &quot;solution id&quot;
with an underscode(&quot;_&quot;) followed by a unique integer (in ascending
order) appended to the give solution id name.

If you look in the xml file output from the flame.save function, the
tag &quot;solution id&quot; will give the
approriate values for the arguments to the restore function.  For
example if you run the &quot;flame1.py&quot; 
demo twice you get to solutions with an id = &quot;solution&quot; and the second
with an id = &quot;solution_2&quot;

Dave


